result.execSummary:
The defendant Telly A Flunder was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>40g), a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)4.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Length of confinement and length of extended supervision for a total length 
of 10 years bifurcated sentence.

Defendant is not eligible for CIP.
Defendant is eligible for SAP after serving 75% of his confinement time.
Conditions, if revoked, are as those outlined in probation conditions.
Supervision may be served in Illinois if they accept him.

miscConds.notes: Defendant must pay court costs, extradition fees of $650.00 and the cost of supervision.    Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law if not previously provided.  Defendant must pay mandatory DNA surcharge.    If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  Apply bond.

Defendant must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment.  If the defendant needs to find a job or loses his job he must conduct a job search and document that search.  Defendant must copy his agent with his search documentation.

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations. 
No alcohol or controlled substances in possession or use, random UA's at discretion of agent.  Do not associate with any known drug dealers or users.  Defendant may only take medication pursuant to a prescription.

Defendant must obey all rules and reguations while on supervision.
Firearms warning given.
Voting prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored.
Appeal rights given.
